OpenAL License
==============

OpenAL is provided under the LGPL (GNU Lesser General Public License)

LGPL License Summary:
The GNU Lesser General Public License (LGPL) allows proprietary use
while requiring that:
- Modifications to OpenAL source code be made available
- The library can be linked against proprietary applications
- A copy of the LGPL license be provided with distributions

For the full LGPL license text, see:
https://www.gnu.org/licenses/lgpl-3.0.html

OpenAL Official Repository:
https://github.com/kcat/openal-soft

License File:
The full LGPL license text is available in the OpenAL-Soft repository.

Additional Notes:
- OpenAL is widely used for cross-platform audio
- OpenAL Soft is an open-source implementation
- Some platforms provide proprietary OpenAL implementations
